It is stronger than steel, lighter than steel and costs less than steel - and now it is so much more than just a theory.  A new company, InventWood has been set up and has over $50 million dollars in funding to turn their research into practical products.

Superwood is Densified wood that is created through a couple of simple processes that increase it's strength while keeping the natural warmth of real wood. snippet.title: Do Thin Oils Destroy Engines? Lessons From GM’s Massive Recall
snippet.description:
After 28,000 engine failures, GM is recommending thicker oil. Will it work?
Do Thin Oils Damage Engines - https://youtu.be/IKdhgKUZhPA
Subscribe to Engineering Explained for more videos! - https://goo.gl/VZstk7

After over 28,000 reported engine failures, GM is recommending thicker oil as a potential solution — but is that really the answer? In this video, we take a deep dive into why so many GM 6.2L V8 (L87) engines are failing, what the actual root causes are, and why a simple oil change is being offered as a fix in some cases.

We’ll explore:
1. The manufacturing flaws behind these widespread failures.
2. How oil viscosity and the Stribeck Curve relate to engine wear.
3. Whether thinner oils are causing damage in modern engines.
4. If switching to a thicker oil could actually help protect your engine.

This isn’t just opinion — we’re digging into the data, published research, and real-world test results to understand the logic behind GM’s service bulletins and what it means for both affected vehicles and the broader debate around oil viscosity. If you’re curious about the science behind engine lubrication, the role of modern manufacturing, or just want to understand what oil you should be using, this video is for you.

Related Videos:

GM Engine Recall Motor Oil Geek - https://youtu.be/pbEdr6Q6cKw

snippet.title: Carín León, Maluma - Si Tú Me Vieras [Official Video]
snippet.description:
🦁 Suscríbete a mi canal: 

Mi nuevo álbum “Palabra de To’s (Seca)" ya está disponible en todas las plataformas: 
https://carinleon.lnk.to/PalabraDeTosSeca

LETRA👇:

Tengo un millón de personas y me siento solitario,
porque no siento tu aroma,
porque no siento tus labios.

De tanto estar desvelado, 
ya se me cambió el horario,
y yo no sé si tú recuerdas,
ayer fue el aniversario.
Todavía me lo recuerda el calendario,
aunque hace daño.

Si tú me vieras cómo tomo,para ver si borracho te olvido.
Si tú me vieras cómo sufro,asimilando que no estás conmigo.
Si tú me vieras, malgastándome las horas viendo nuestras fotos.
Si tú me vieras, cómo hablo con el silencio cosas de nosotros.
Si tú me vieras,si tú me vieras...
Seguramente otra oportunidad me dieras.

Reina,vuelva.
Hagamos que lo nuestro se resuelva.
Si algo de mí en tu vida se conserva, 
entoncesvamos a intentarlo de nuevo.
Tomando a tu nombre, una semana llevo.
Yo sé que superarte debo,
pero tu nombre vuelve cuando bebo.

Aunque no parezca,
estoy hablando con el corazón, 
para que te compadezcas.
Ya tomaste tu decisión, pero...

Si tú me vieras cómo tomo,para ver si borracho te olvido.
Si tú me vieras cómo sufro,asimilando que no estás conmigo.
Si tú me vieras, malgastándome las horas viendo nuestras fotos.
Si tú me vieras, cómo hablo con el silencio cosas de nosotros.
Si tú me vieras,si tú me vieras...


Seguramente otra oportunidad me dieras.

snippet.title: Lion Digs Inside Tree to Get to Leopard Cub that’s Hiding
snippet.description:
A pair of lionesses spot a mother leopard and her cub with a warthog in a tree. The lions climb up the tree and chase them away from their food, but the cub doesn’t have time to escape and so is forced to hide in a cavity in the tree. 
Smelling the little one, the lioness tries her best to dig in the tree and reach for the baby, but will it escape with its life or is its fate sealed?

snippet.title: I Challenged Morgan Wallen to a Golf Match
snippet.description:
Last week we headed out to Troubadour Golf an Field Club  in Tennessee to play 9 holes with my buddy Morgan Wallen a few days before his album released. Turns out neither of us like to lose... 

What I enjoyed the most was listening to Morgan talk about his journey with music, I think you'll find it pretty interesting too. 

Go stream "I'm The Problem" out everywhere now... album of the year!
